PetPal – Pet Activity Tracker

PetPal is a micro-app that helps pet parents track their pet’s daily activities, get smart reminders, and interact with an AI assistant for contextual pet care insights.

Tech Stack

Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite

UI: Shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS

Backend: Express.js + TypeScript

State Management: TanStack Query (for server state)

Routing: Wouter (lightweight client-side routing)

Storage: In-memory (easily replaceable with a database)

Features

Login flow with responsive, mobile-first design

Activity logging: walks, meals, and medications

Daily summary with numeric and visual representation of activities

AI pet assistant with contextual memory of chat history

Reminder if no walk has been logged by 18:00 local time

Clean and accessible user interface with smooth animations

Run Locally
Backend
cd backend
npm install
npm run dev

Frontend
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev


Open http://localhost:5173
 to view the app.
Backend runs on http://localhost:5000.

Trade-offs

In-memory storage is used for simplicity (resets on restart).

AI chatbot is rule-based for fast implementation; can be extended with NLP.

Mobile-first UI design prioritized; desktop layout is minimal.
